## Architectural Issues & Tech Debt

> [!WARNING]
> ### No Proper Routing
> The entire app runs from a **single `index.tsx`** file using manual `useState` for tab switching and conditional rendering. There's no `expo-router` tab layout despite it being installed and mentioned in the plan. This means:
> - No URL-based navigation, no deep linking
> - No back button support on Android
> - No screen transitions or animations
> - All sub-screens are rendered via state toggling inside components

**Recommendation**: Migrate to proper `expo-router` file-based routing with:
- `src/app/(onboarding)/` group for onboarding flow
- `src/app/(tabs)/` group for the main tab navigation
- `src/app/(screens)/` group for detail screens (medications, goals, etc.)

---

> [!WARNING]
> ### No Proper Typography
> The HTML designs use `Bodoni Moda` (headlines) and `Lexend` (body) fonts. The React Native app uses system fonts only (`fontFamily: 'System'`). This significantly degrades the premium look.

**Recommendation**: Install custom fonts via `expo-font` and load `Bodoni Moda` + `Lexend` from Google Fonts assets.

