## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **Routing migration priority**: Should we migrate to proper `expo-router` file-based routing first (which will touch every file), or build new screens first and migrate later?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 2. **Which design style**: Your `Suvi Health app Ui/` folder has both original and `_new_style` variants for Welcome, Goals, Profile, and Permissions. Which style should we follow for the React Native implementation?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 3. **AI integration**: The chat currently uses hardcoded keyword-matched responses. Do you want to integrate a real AI backend (e.g., Gemini API) for the chat, symptom assessment, and report analysis, or keep it as a polished mock/prototype?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 4. **Data persistence scope**: Currently everything is stored in AsyncStorage. For features like Health Vault documents and appointment scheduling, should we plan for a backend (Firebase/Supabase) or keep everything local?

